{"cursor":"3464","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox military person |name=Titus Pullo |birth_date= |death_date=\n|birth_place= |death_place= |image=DE BELLO GALL.JPG |caption= A page 118 of\nJulius Caesar's Commentarii de Bello Gallico with description of actions of T.\nPulfio & L. Varenus |nickname= |allegiance=Julius Caesar, later Pompey |branch=\n|serviceyears= |rank=Centurion |commands= |unit=Legio XXIV Vixtrix Rapax\n|battles=Battle of Pharsalus |laterwork= }} 'Titus Pullo' His [[Roman naming\nconvention|nomen]] is given as Pulfio, Puleio, Pullio, Pulcio or Pulcia in\nvarious manuscripts. was one of the two Roman centurions of the 11th\nLegion (Legio XI Claudia) mentioned in the writings of Julius Caesar. The other\nsoldier mentioned was Lucius Vorenus; they appear in Caesar's [[Commentarii de\nBello Gallico]], Book 5, Chapter 44. Pullo and Vorenus were fierce rivals for\npromotion to [[primus pilus]], the most senior centurion in a legion. Both\ndistinguished themselves in 54 BC when the Nervii attacked the legion under\nQuintus Cicero in their winter quarters in Nervian territory. In an effort to\noutdo Vorenus, Pullo charged out of the fortified camp and attacked the enemy,\nbut was soon wounded and surrounded. Vorenus followed and engaged his attackers\nin hand-to-hand combat, killing one and driving the rest back, but lost his\nfooting and was himself soon surrounded. Pullo in turn rescued Vorenus, and\nafter killing several of the enemy, the pair returned to camp amid applause from\ntheir comrades. Julius Caesar, [[Commentarii de Bello Gallico]] \n\nIn the Civil War of 49 BC, Pullo was assigned to the XXIV Victrix Rapax, a new\nItalian legion commanded by the legate Gaius Antonius. In 48 BC, Antonius was\nblockaded on an island and forced to surrender; Pullo was apparently responsible\nfor most of his soldiers switching sides to fight for Pompey. Later that year,\nhe is recorded bravely defending Pompey's camp in Greece from Caesar's attack\nshortly before the Battle of Pharsalus. Dio Cassius, Roman History\n[http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Cassius_Dio/41*.html#40\n41.40]; Julius Caesar, [[Commentarii de Bello Civili]] \n","linknr":130,"url":"Titus_Pullo","recorded":1375083747,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Titus_Pullo&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Titus_Pullo&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Titus_Pullo_(Rome_character)","/wiki/File:DE_BELLO_GALL.JPG","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/19/DE_BELLO_GALL.JPG/220px-DE_BELLO_GALL.JPG","/wiki/Julius_Caesar","/wiki/Julius_Caesar","/wiki/Pompey","/wiki/Centurion","/w/index.php?title=Legio_XXIV_Vixtrix_Rapax&action=edit&redlink=1","/wiki/Battle_of_Pharsalus","#cite_note-1","/wiki/Roman_Republic","/wiki/Centurion","/wiki/Roman_legion","/wiki/Legio_XI_Claudia","/wiki/Julius_Caesar","/wiki/Lucius_Vorenus","/wiki/Commentarii_de_Bello_Gallico","/wiki/Primus_pilus","/wiki/Nervii","/wiki/Quintus_Tullius_Cicero","#cite_note-2","/wiki/Caesar%27s_civil_war","/wiki/Legatus","/wiki/Gaius_Antonius","/wiki/Pompey","/wiki/Battle_of_Pharsalus","#cite_note-3","/w/index.php?title=Titus_Pullo&action=edit&section=1","/wiki/Titus_Pullo_(character_of_Rome)